#2304
Stone Chamber~
   The long stone hall ends in a stone chamber furnished only with cracked,
moldering tables on which lie rusted implements of iron.  Rain falls into the
middle of the room from a shaft in the ceiling that must run all the way to the
top of the tor.  From the bottom of the shaft dangles a rope, swinging slightly.
A drain in the center of the floor allows the water to escape, but old, dark
stains suggest that it was used to carry away other fluids long ago.
